{"data":{"docBySlug":{"html":"<h1 id=\"outline-shader-module\"><a href=\"#outline-shader-module\" aria-label=\"outline shader module permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Outline (Shader Module)</h1>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">outline</code> module is useful when you are rendering 2D elements in the same plane (on top of each other), but want to show some kind of outline or shadow to indicate which element is logically on top.</p>\n<p>Implementation note: This module works by rendering your graphics into a sample \"outline\" shadow map, and then darkens the color on pixels in your graphics when they are drawn close to another object with a higher \"logical z order\", giving a shadow outline effect.</p>\n<h2 id=\"usage\"><a href=\"#usage\" aria-label=\"usage permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Usage</h2>\n<p>Your vertex shader might look like:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">attribute vec3 position;\nattribute vec4 lineColor;\nattribute float zLevel;\n\nvarying vec4 vColor;\n\nvoid main() {\n  ...\n\n  gl_Position = projectionMatrix * modelViewMatrix * vec4(position, 1);\n  vColor = lineColor;\n\n  ...\n\n  // Store info needed to render outline shadows\n  outline_setZLevel(zLevel);\n  outline_setUV(gl_Position);\n}</code></pre></div>\n<p>And in the fragment shader:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">varying vec4 vColor;\n\nvoid main() {\n  gl_FragColor = vColor;\n\n  ...\n\n  // Render outline shadows\n  gl_FragColor = outline_filterColor(gl_FragColor);\n\n  ...\n}</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"getuniforms\"><a href=\"#getuniforms\" aria-label=\"getuniforms permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>getUniforms</h2>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">getUniforms({outlineRender, outlineShadowMap})</code></p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">outlineRender</code> (Boolean, <code class=\"language-text\">false</code>) - set to <code class=\"language-text\">true</code> during the \"outline map\" rendering pass (i.e. specifies whether to render into or from the shadowmap).</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">outlineShadowmap</code> (<code class=\"language-text\">Texture</code>, required) -</li>\n</ul>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"Outline (Shader Module)The  module is useful when you are rendering 2D elements in the same plane (on top of each other), but want to showâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"Outline (Shader Module)","cover":"cover","category":"docs","tags":["default"]}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"relativeLinks":{"../../../faq.md":"/docs/faq","docs/faq.md":"/docs/faq","../../../faq":"/docs/faq","docs/faq":"/docs/faq","../../../roadmap.md":"/docs/roadmap","docs/roadmap.md":"/docs/roadmap","../../../roadmap":"/docs/roadmap","docs/roadmap":"/docs/roadmap","../../../README.md":"/docs","docs/README.md":"/docs","../../..":"/docs","docs":"/docs","../../../get-started/basic-usage.md":"/docs/get-started/basic-usage","docs/get-started/basic-usage.md":"/docs/get-started/basic-usage","../../../get-started/basic-usage":"/docs/get-started/basic-usage","docs/get-started/basic-usage":"/docs/get-started/basic-usage","../../../get-started/html-overlays.md":"/docs/get-started/html-overlays","docs/get-started/html-overlays.md":"/docs/get-started/html-overlays","../../../get-started/html-overlays":"/docs/get-started/html-overlays","docs/get-started/html-overlays":"/docs/get-started/html-overlays","../../../interactive-examples/world-heritage.md":"/docs/interactive-examples/world-heritage","docs/interactive-examples/world-heritage.md":"/docs/interactive-examples/world-heritage","../../../interactive-examples/world-heritage":"/docs/interactive-examples/world-heritage","docs/interactive-examples/world-heritage":"/docs/interactive-examples/world-heritage","../mesh-layer.md":"/docs/api-reference/layers/mesh-layer","docs/api-reference/layers/mesh-layer.md":"/docs/api-reference/layers/mesh-layer","../mesh-layer":"/docs/api-reference/layers/mesh-layer","docs/api-reference/layers/mesh-layer":"/docs/api-reference/layers/mesh-layer","../editable-geojson-layer.md":"/docs/api-reference/layers/editable-geojson-layer","docs/api-reference/layers/editable-geojson-layer.md":"/docs/api-reference/layers/editable-geojson-layer","../editable-geojson-layer":"/docs/api-reference/layers/editable-geojson-layer","docs/api-reference/layers/editable-geojson-layer":"/docs/api-reference/layers/editab